<Link id="l00119" /><CodeLine lineNumber="119"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00120" /><CodeLine lineNumber="120"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// A directive&#39;s supplied pattern is said to be either expected or excluded</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="121"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// depending on whether the pattern must have or must not have a match in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="122"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// order for the directive to succeed.  For example, a CHECK directive&#39;s</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="123"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// pattern is expected, and a CHECK-NOT directive&#39;s pattern is excluded.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="124"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="125"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// There might be more than one match result for a single pattern.  For</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="126"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// example, there might be several discarded matches</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="127"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// (MatchFoundButDiscarded) before either a good match</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="128"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// (MatchFoundAndExpected) or a failure to match (MatchNoneButExpected),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="129"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// and there might be a fuzzy match (MatchFuzzy) after the latter.</span></CodeLine>
